				<wikidot:authorName>Crow-Cat</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3952131</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>If I'm getting this right&#8230;</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Spoilers</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Close</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>The spirals are supposed to signify Pattern Screamers? I feel like spirals have been used to represent them for awhile but I can't think of any specifics. I know the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-2651">SCP-2651</a> species is only briefly mentioned here and isn't really related to the article, but when they're referred to as 'Venusians,' coupled with the possible Pattern-Screamer=spiral motif, I thought you making a connection to <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-1694">SCP-1694</a>. But I wasn't really sure since not a lot of people recognize it as a Pattern Screamer article.</p> <p>But today I saw SCP-002-EX was connected to <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-1795">SCP-1795</a> on the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-series-2-tales-edition">Series 2 Tales</a> list, and the 'Pattern Screamers=spirals' idea popped into my head again.</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
